		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Wizard Skill Improvement</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Azzigoth</a> | 
		            8/24/1999 6:55:31 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Quick Guide to Improving your Wizard's Skills.<BR>
As a wizard your spells are your weapons.<BR>
Just as a warrior you must be proficient in their use.<BR>
I make it a point to keep my skill levels maxed in 3 of the 4 schools of magical skills.<BR>
Your skill max is determined by your level.  The formula is simple.<BR>
Skill Max = (lvl x 5) + 5<BR>
ie for a lvl 12 wizard, Skill Max = (12x5) + 5 = 65<BR>
<BR>
To improve:<BR>
<BR>
Alteration - needed for Root, etc<BR>
Memorize Fade and Shadow Step spells.<BR>
On a full bar of mana, alternate between casting these two spells.<BR>
By using the two spells alternating you avoid waiting for it to recover.<BR>
I RECOMMEND you do this in a safe zone.<BR>
It will take some time, but with a high alteration skill, those roots should be a bit more successful.<BR>
(this tip from another site that I now forget)<BR>
<BR>
Evocation - your DD spells<BR>
Normally will go up on their own.<BR>
<BR>
Abjuration - defensive spells<BR>
I normally memorize and repeatedly cast minor shielding on myself.<BR>
Even if your currently using a higher level shielding spell, the low cost of 10 mana for minor shielding, should allow you to cast it a lot.<BR>
Another method is to mem and cast Okiel's Raditation on your party tanks a lot.  At 15 mana it costs more, but can be used as you play.<BR>
<BR>
Divination - useless initially but inevitably needed for invisibility<BR>
I mem sense summoned and cast it repeatedly.<BR>
<BR>
Conjuration - not very useful yet<BR>
My skill in conjuration is very low, and I have not found an effective way to increase it.<BR>
<BR>
Swimming - do it a lot<BR>
<BR>
Sense Heading - click it A LOT, boat rides are a good time and while your medding.<BR>
It's always good to have your bearings.<BR>
<BR>
Meditation - will increase on its own<BR>
<BR>
Once you get your basic skills up to the max, as you level it will not be as difficult to raise them the 5 points.<BR>
<BR>
Many wizards I know neglect their alteration and divination skills.  Investing the time to raise them and keep them maxed is important.<BR>
<BR>
1HB, 2HB, Piercing - Once you reach a high level your need for these will disappear.<BR>
Although many wizards consider it a waste of their time to melee, I think it is very important.<BR>
It will show your group members that your not afraid to get dirty and bash monsters with them.<BR>
I normally wade into the melee when the monster is down to its last 1/4 of health.  It is an opportunity to increase your melee, offense and defence skills.<BR>
<BR>
Azzigoth High Elven Wizard E'ci
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
